inds is that Ford used music as more than a stylistic gesture. In fascinating discussions of Ford's westerns—from silent-era features such as Straight Shooting and The Iron Horse to classics of the sound era such as My Darling Clementine and The Searchers —Kalinak describes how the director exploited music, and especially song, in defining the geographical and ideological space of the American West.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMotion picture musiczUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  a20th century american film.  aamerican cinema.  aamerican film director.  aamerican filmmakers.  aamerican folk music.  aamerican folk songs.  aamerican west.  abiographical.  acinema.  afilm criticism.  afilm studies.  afilm.  ahollywood.  ahymnody.  ajohn ford.  amovie studies.  amovie.  amusic in film.  amusic.  amy darling clementine.  aold west.  aperiod music.  astagecoach.  athe iron horse.  athe man who shot liberty valance.  athe searchers.  awestern films.  awestern united states.  awesterns.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025234940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094107640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520941076423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520941076/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY